com.navis.framework.portal.query

Interface DataQuery

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BasicQuery, Bounded, ExecutableQuery, Ordered, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DomainQuery, ISavedQuery
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataQuery, DomainQueryImpl, FinderQuery, NullDataQuery, NullDomainQuery, SimpleSavedQuery

    public interface DataQuery
extends java.io.Serializable, ExecutableQuery
    An base interface describing a Query. Encapsulates only the ideas that a query may be: 1) bounded, 2) have a set of desired fields, 3) have a desired ordering of those fields.

    • Method Detail

      • createEnhanceableClone

        @Nullable
DataQuery createEnhanceableClone()
        Cloning method: clones a DomainQuery so it can be 'enhanced' prior to execution. This allows addition of predicates to the DomainQuery for execution, without affecting the original.
        Returns:
        cloned query

      • createEnhanceableCloneWithoutPredicates

        @Nullable
DataQuery createEnhanceableCloneWithoutPredicates()
        Cloning method: clones a DomainQuery so it can be 'enhanced' prior to execute. This method doesn not add the predicates (used when we already have our primary keys - e.g., filter).
        Returns:
        A cloned DomainQuery without predicates.

      • isTotalCountRequired

        boolean isTotalCountRequired()
        Returns:
        FALSE if we don't need to count total number of records. The default value should be TRUE. Most views with UI should count total.

      • setRequireTotalCount

        void setRequireTotalCount(boolean inRequiresTotalCount)
        Set if counting of total records is required. In case of API without UI it might be set to FALSE. This will eliminate unecessary counting and improve application performance
        Parameters:
        inRequiresTotalCount - required total count
